<title>NEW ZEALAND: Power NZ says to consider bid.</title>
<headline>Power NZ says to consider bid.</headline>
<dateline>WELLINGTON 1997-05-20</dateline>
<text>
<p>Power New Zealand said it was advised on Tuesday morning that its two major shareholders, Utilicorp NZ and Mercury Energy, were to form a joint venture to hold their shareholdings in Power New Zealand and were offering NZ$6.00 a share to the company's minority shareholders.</p>
<p>&quot;The board of Power New Zealand will be meeting with its major shareholders on these matters prior to its scheduled board meeting this Thursday and expects it will be in a position to make a statement to the market following this.&quot;</p>
<p>-- Wellington newsroom 64 4 4734 746</p>
